Hallo.

On a linux mint system, I'm writing a document in XML. My problem is
the font setting.

I have the font set, say, "Rosana Serif" in the usual fonts directory
"~/.fonts/rosana/", and a copy of the same fonts in a sub-directory of
my working directory: "fonts".

Well, if I set the font-face in the following way:

   @font-face {
       font-family: 'Rosana';
       src: url('fonts/Rosana-Regular.otf') format('opentype');
       font-weight: normal;
       font-style: normal;}

it works well, but if I refer the font-face to the system fonts like this:

   @font-face {
       font-family: 'Rosana';
       src: url('~/.fonts/rosana/Rosana-Regular.otf') format('opentype');
       /* 
       font-weight: normal;
       font-style: normal;}